=Phnompenhpost.com |date=2013-06-19 |accessdate=2013-12-02}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Madra |first=Ek |url=http://uk.reuters.com/article/2008/04/22/soccer-asia-cambodia-idUKSP32748520080422 |title=Soccer-Cambodia to beef-up national team to stem goals tide &#124; Reuters |publisher=Uk.reuters.com |date=2008-04-22 |accessdate=2013-12-02}}</ref> Football is the most popular sport in Cambodia, although [[Sepak takraw]] (which looks like volleyball), mixed martial arts and wrestling are also popular.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.topendsports.com/world/countries/cambodia.htm|title=Sport in Cambodia|website=www.topendsports.com|language=en|access-date=2018-09-04}}</ref>\n\n==National team==\n\nThe national team's best performance was at the [[1972 AFC Asian Cup]] where they reached the semi finals.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|1}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://video.ppsoccer.com/ Soccer Highlights]\n\n{{Football in Cambodia}}\n{{Asia in topic|Football in}}\n\n[[Category:Football in Cambodia| ]]\n\n\n{{Cambodia-sport-stub}}\n{{footy-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox sport overview\n| boxwidth      = 250\n| title         = Football in Cambodia\n| image         = \n| imagesize     = 240px\n| image_alt     = <!-- alt text, which will be seen when hovering over the image -->\n| caption       = \n| union         = [[Football Federation of Cambodia|Cambodian Football Federation]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ffcambodia.com/|title=The Achievements of Cambodia Football Team|website=www.ffcambodia.com}}</ref>\n| country       = Cambodia\n| sport         = association football\n| noncountry    = <!-- other country this country represents -->\n| teamlabel1    = <!-- overrides the \"National team\" label with custom label -->\n| nationalteam  = [[Cambodia national football team|men's national team]]\n| teamlabel2    = <!-- overrides the \"Representative team\" label with customer label -->\n| repteam       = <!-- overrides the representative team link, requires full wikitext sy