e.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mathrubhumi.com/english/story.php?id=106502 |title=1,373 nominations for Kerala polls |publisher=Mathrubhumi English |date=27 March 2011 |accessdate=16 May 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120328122509/http://www.mathrubhumi.com/english/story.php?id=106502 |archivedate=28 March 2012 }}</ref>\n\nA total of 971 candidates contested the elections, after the withdrawal of nominations closed.<ref name=\"mathrubhumi1\"/>\n\n===Voting===\n\nThe polling to elect members of assembly from the 140 constituencies in [[Kerala]] was held successfully on 13 April 2011. 75.12 per cent voter turn out was recorded in the state. The district wise and constituency wise polling percentage is as given below.<ref>http://www.ceo.kerala.gov.in/pdf/generalelection2011/GE2011_VT_REP.pdf</ref><ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.thehindu.com/multimedia/archive/00551/Polling_Percentages_551834a.pdf | title=HP-LA Polling Percentage | location=Chennai, India | work=The Hindu}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable collapsible\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | Sl. No:\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | Constituency\n! scope=\"col\" | No. of Voters\n! scope=\"col\" | Polling Stations\n! scope=\"col\" | Percentage of Polling\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\" |[[Kasaragod district|'''Kasaragod''']]||'''76.3%'''\n|-\n| 1 ||[[Manjeshwar (State Assembly constituency)|Manjeshwar]]|| 176801 || 160 || 75.1%\n|-\n| 2 ||[[Kasaragod (State Assembly constituency)|Kasargod]]|| 159251 || 140 || 73.6%\n|-\n| 3 ||[[Udma (State Assembly constituency)|Udma]]|| 173441 || 152 || 74.0%\n|-\n| 4 ||[[Kanhangad (State Assembly constituency)|Kanhangad]]|| 177812 || 158 || 78.4%\n|-\n| 5 ||[[Thrikaripur (State Assembly constituency)|Trikaripur]]|| 169019 || 162 || 80.4%\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\" |[[Kannur district|'''Kannur''']]||'''80.7%'''\n|-\n| 6 ||[[Payyanur (State Assembly constituency)|Payyannur]]|| 157667 || 151 || 82.3%\n|-\n| 7 ||[[Kalliasseri (State Assembly constituency)|Ka