<ref name=\":6\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.madhyamam.com/news/77226/110510|title=\u0d2f\u0d41.\u0d21\u0d3f.\u0d0e\u0d2b\u0d4d \u0d05\u0d27\u0d3f\u0d15\u0d3e\u0d30\u0d24\u0d4d\u0d24\u0d3f\u0d32\u0d47\u0d15\u0d4d\u0d15\u0d46\u0d28\u0d4d\u0d28\u0d4d \u0d38\u0d30\u0d4d\u200d\u0d35\u0d47\u0d15\u0d33\u0d4d\u200d {{!}} Madhyamam|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110512054749/http://www.madhyamam.com/news/77226/110510|archive-date=12 May 2011|access-date=11 May 2011|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n|''News24 channel -Today's Chanakya Agency''\n|84 - 102\n|35 - 53\n|0 - 6\n|-\n|\n|<ref name=\":7\">{{cite web|url=http://www.rediff.com/news/slide-show/slide-show-1-tn-assembly-exit-poll/20110510.htm|title=Exit poll: DMK routed, Left loses Kerala, Bengal&nbsp;\u2013 Rediff.com News|date=10 May 2011|publisher=Rediff.com|accessdate=16 May 2011}}</ref>\n|''CVB News-C-Voter''\n|49 - 57\n|83 - 91\n|1 - 4\n|}\n\n* \n\n==Election==\nThe thirteenth legislative assembly election was held on 13 April 2011.\nThe filing of nominations for the elections ended on 26 March 2011. A total of 1373 contestants filed nominations.\nThe scrutiny of nominations took place on 29 March 2011.\nAccording to the latest revised electoral list, there are a total of 22,878,767 voters, with 11,919,652 women and 10,959,115 men. There are 20,758 polling booths in 11,662 polling locations in the state.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mathrubhumi.com/english/story.php?id=106502 |title=1,373 nominations for Kerala polls |publisher=Mathrubhumi English |date=27 March 2011 |accessdate=16 May 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120328122509/http://www.mathrubhumi.com/english/story.php?id=106502 |archivedate=28 March 2012 }}</ref>\n\nA total of 971 candidates contested the elections, after the withdrawal of nominations closed.<ref name=\"mathrubhumi1\"/>\n\n===Voting===\n\nThe polling to elect members of assembly from the 140 constituencies in [[Kerala]] was held successfully on 13 April 2011. 75.12 per cent voter turn out was recorded in the state. The district wise and constituency wise polling percentage is as given below.<ref>http://www.ceo.kerala.gov.in/pdf/generalelection2011/GE2011_VT_REP.pdf</ref><ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.thehindu.com/multimedia/archive/00551/Polling_Percentages_551834a.pdf | title=HP-LA Polling Percentage | location=Chennai, India | work=The Hindu}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable collapsible\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | Sl. No:\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | Constituency\n! scope=\"col\" | No. of Voters\n! scope=\"col\" | Polling Stations\n! scope=\"col\" | Percentage of Polling\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\" |[[Kasaragod district|'''Kasaragod''']]||'''76.3%'''\n|-\n| 1 ||[[Manjeshwar (State Assembly constituency)|Manjeshwar]]|| 176801 || 160 || 75.1%\n|-\n| 2 ||[[Kasaragod (State Assembly constituency)|Kasargod]]|| 159251 || 140 || 73.6%\n|-\n| 3 ||[[Udma (State Assembly constituency)|Udma]]|| 173441 || 152 || 74.0%\n|-\n| 4 ||[[Kanhangad (State Assembly constituency)|Kanhangad]]|| 177812 || 158 || 78.4%\n|-\n| 5 ||[[Thrikaripur (State Assembly constituency)|Trikaripur]]|| 169019 || 162 || 80.4%\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\" |[[Kannur district|'''Kannur''']]||'''80.7%'''\n|-\n| 6 ||[[Payyanur (State Assembly constituency)|Payyannur]]|| 157667 || 151 || 82.3%\n|-\n| 7 ||[[Kalliasseri (State Assembly constituency)|Kalliasseri]]|| 156598 || 148 || 79.4%\n|-\n| 8 ||[[Taliparamba (State Assembly constituency)|Taliparamba]]|| 173593 || 161 || 82.7%\n|-\n| 9 ||[[Irikkur (State Assembly constituency)|Irikkur]]|| 168376 || 163 || 77.3%\n|-\n| 10 ||[[Azhikode (State Assembly constituency)|Azhikode]]|| 147413 || 128 || 82.2%\n|-\n| 11 ||[[Kannur (State Assembly constituency)|Kannur]]|| 143181 || 122 || 78.7%\n|-\n| 12 ||[[Dharmadom (State Assembly constituency)|Dharmadam]]|| 162161 || 139 || 83.4%\n|-\n| 13 ||[[Thalassery (State Assembly constituency)|Thalassery]]|| 149174 || 144 || 78.6%\n|-\n| 14 ||[[Kuthuparamba (State Assem